reviews.text: Taste good & Service good👍👍👍

Well..... The food is good😒, but service is bad and there is a deadline to eat for 75 minutes, the place is almost empty, the milk you put on the mango pudding has been opened for ages and the pudding is lumpy, and you can't pay with credit card until you buy food worth $200HKD.👎👎👎😒😣☹️😕😱😵🤢🤮😖🤬

We went for dim sum on a Sunday at around 12:30. We got a table immediately though it took about 5 min to set up. Once we sat down, we had only 75 min to finish our meal as stated on a notice at the entrance ( if 8 people or fewer, 75 min, if above then 90 min). I thought it was too short a time but my friends wanted to have yum cha.  Ok let's give it a try... it wasn't too rush after all???  Oop... no, just because it wasn't too full today (due to the rainly weather??) they didn't ask us to leave. We took 105 min to finish this meal after all!!!!!

The food is above average but so is the price.  Problem is there was definitely a shortage of staff and it was pretty hard to gt anything. We needed some chilli sauce and asked for it but it never came. So my friend went to the counter to get it herself but was told off by the waitress, not a very nice experience indeed.

Not a place I would return to unless absolutely necessary.
satisfied with food quality n service.  Ingredients were highly fresh.   GOOD

result.name: 囍粵

reviews.text: 菜肉雲吞湯麵真下九流,肉不鲜有霉味,湯底盬油水還上得菜单推介?中伏了!其他点心尚可,但价錢唔平
地方幽静，方便，食物和價錢可接受，不算貴也不算太平。
價錢貴。服務一般，最不滿是很多次明明有幾張以上空枱都係要你搭枱(share table),但係到你走果時根本都冇人坐既，今日又係咁，有個抱住BB黎，都要叫人地坐埋黎我地張枱，明明後面有4張冇人枱。註：果時冇人排隊的，好奇怪！
位置適中 地方不大 佈局合理 尚算整潔 燈光舒眼 食物味道中上 服務尚可 價錢中上 性價比合理
下午茶很便宜，地方都不錯，食品可以。
